   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2410_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>


               <address>
                  <addrLine>Girls' High School,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Lytham Rd.,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Blackpool.</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1925-03-06">6.3.25.</date>
               </dateline>

               <salute> Dear Mr Hardy,</salute>

            </opener>

            <p>I'm very sorry to trouble you, but I have been wondering whether you can tell me
               where the "<placeName ref="#pl:BeenyCliff"><choice><sic>Cliff without a name</sic>
                     <corr>Cliff without a Name</corr></choice></placeName>" is. It appears on the
               maps, and as far as I remember it is mentioned in <ref target="#bib:Hardy1891_Tess"
                  >Tess of the d'Urbervilles</ref>.</p>

            <p> I am very interested in it as I live in <placeName ref="#pl:Bude">Bude</placeName>,
               and know that particular part of the coast fairly well.</p>


            <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2410_2.jpg"/>
            <pb n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2410_3.jpg"/>
            <p>Hoping I am not giving you a great deal of trouble.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>I remain</salute>
               <salute>Yours Sincerely,</salute>
               <signed>Marie Flower.</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2410_4.jpg"/>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="reply" hand="unknown">
            <!-- check with Angelique/Phillip -->
            <p>The "<placeName ref="#pl:BeenyCliff"><choice><sic>Cliff without a name</sic>
                     <corr>Cliff without a Name</corr></choice></placeName>"^ <add place="above">in
                     <ref target="#bib:Hardy1873_PairOfBlueEyes">A Pair of Blue Eyes</ref></add>, so
               far as it is anywhere , is near <placeName ref="#pl:BeenyCliff">Beeny</placeName>,
               about a mile from <placeName ref="#pl:Boscastle">Boscastle</placeName>. See <persName
                  ref="#ps:TH">Mr Hardy</persName>'s "<ref target="#bib:Hardy1919_CollectedPoems"
                  >Collected Poems</ref>"; 1 vol. (<orgName ref="#ps:Macmillan">Macmillan &amp; Co
                  publishers</orgName>).</p>
